fix(D5): Addressed GitHub Copilot review comments
Improved webpack plugin implementation based on code review feedback:
Race Condition Fixes: - Replaced forEach with Promise.all() and async/await pattern to prevent race conditions when processing multiple conversion outline files - Ensured single callback execution to webpack compiler preventing multiple completion signals
Async Operations: - Changed from fs.writeFileSync to fs.promises.writeFile for consistency with async pattern and to prevent blocking the event loop - Added proper error propagation through Promise.all catch chain
Code Quality Improvements: - Replaced fragile element.type.includes('Literal') with explicit array of valid literal types for more robust AST node type checking - Extracted firstDefined() utility function to reduce code duplication in extractArrayElements and extractValue functions
All functionality preserved while making the code more robust, performant, and maintainable for production use.
Ref: elegantthemes/Divi#44955

feat(D5): Added automated JSON generation for conversion outline
Implemented ConversionOutlineJsonPlugin webpack plugin to automatically generate conversion-outline.json files from conversion-outline.ts files during build processes (npm run start/build/zip). This ensures consistency between Divi 5 core modules and extension modules by providing the same automated build workflow.
Added glob and jscodeshift dependencies to enable TypeScript AST parsing and file discovery. Created webpack/config/plugins directory following Divi 5 core patterns with conversion-outline-json-plugin.js and extract-static-properties.js helper. Updated webpack.config.js to integrate the plugin into the build pipeline.
The generated JSON files include the required header comment and match the exact format used by Divi 5 core modules, enabling proper module conversion and backward compatibility.
Fixes: elegantthemes/Divi#44955

Merge pull request #45 from elegantthemes/42110-d5-placeholder-content-module-utils
D5 :: Example Modules :: Fix fatal error due to missing `placeholderContent`

fix(D5, Example Modules, Placeholder Content): use `@divi/module-utils` to import `placeholderContent`.
Recently, we just move the `placeholderContent` from `module` to `module-utils` package. This causes a fatal error on console log when it's being used by example and third-party modules. This issue happens due to the `divi-types` is not updated yet, so the `placeholderContent` is still in `module` package instead of `module-utils` package.
Despite we can simply update the import, the error still exists on build when we run `npm run start`. So, we need to update our `divi-types` fully to make sure we can fix the issue. For note, I added quick note on readme file to make anyone who use this plugin know the error.
Part of elegantthemes/Divi#42110.

feat(D5, Static Module, Settings): introduce some new properties to `module.json` file of Dynamic Module.
### Introduce some new properties to `module.json` file of Dynamic Module.
This is the first step to convert the Manually Generated module settings (composable approach) into Auto Generated module settings in Dynamic Module.
This step will add some new properties: - `moduleClassName` to identify current module class name. - `moduleOrderClassName` to identify current module order class name. - `settings` as a place to set some details for the module settings. This is where we're going to make certain panels into auto generated module settings or adding new groups as needed.
Part of elegantthemes/Divi#41608.
